1,2. harness; roller and scaling hook and rope; yellow moulded plastic with silver plastic additions and hook. 
     1. harness front has the black plastic roller attached.
     2. harness back has a rising arm on the left side which end with the grappling hook and scaling rope. It also has a link to hold the drill (3). The front and back are linked by rubber strapping over the shoulders and under the arms. Marked MADE IN MEXICO c MATTEL 1986 1942-2048 
3. drill; mid brown and silver moulded plastic with a ratchet sound when drill is turned. It has a hook on the side to fasten it to the harness. Marked MEXICO c MATTEL 1986 1942-2088.
4. canopy; clear plastic; marked MADE IN MEXICO c MATTEL 1986 1942-2258. It may fit over the front part to form a face shield 
5. shield; moulded yellow plastic; round with a hand grip at the back. Marked 7997-2229 
6. shield; moulded lime green plastic round with pointed ends in the shape of cobras' heads; hand bar at the back. Marked 1967 c MATTEL 1986 Malaysia 
7. shield; moulded dark blue plastic; round with hand bar at the back. Marked MALAYSIA 
8. shield; moulded dark brown plastic; the same design as (6) 
9. shield; moulded orange plastic with hand grip at the back. Marked 9040-2649 
*10-13. cross bows; moulded plastic; each has an end in the shape of a reptile's face. 
     10. cream; marked 9172-2229 Malaysia 
     11. grey; marked c MATTEL 1984 9168-2139

14. dragonfly which is probably a cross bow; dark green moulded plastic; marked 2331-2039 HONG KONG 
15. axe; mid brown moulded plastic 
16. sword; mid brown moulded plastic 
17. gun; mid brown moulded plastic 
18. gun; orange moulded plastic 
19. gun; silver moulded plastic - this has an end which could fit into a wrist fitting of one of the figures. 
20. long axe; opaque moulded plastic

22. projectile; possibly an arrow or a club; moulded mid brown plastic 23. projectile; possibly an arrow or a club; dark brown moulded plastic 24. lock; green moulded plastic

fields.title: MASTERS OF THE UNIVERSE
fields.object: Equipment for he-man figures and transformers
fields.history_note:
References: Mattel 1985 Catalogue. Masters of the Universe is a boy's fantasy toy group consisting of men; equipment and vehicles based on a main character - HE-MAN. It is said to represent the struggle between good and evil.

Bought by the donor between 1983 and 1987. Mr Dacas was born 17/10/73 and saved his pocket money to buy the toys. He played with them and created his own dramas for the characters. MASTERS OF THE
UNIVERSE was one of the top ten ranges of fantasy toys for four or five years; last seen in the list September 1988.
